snippet.textDisplay: You did so well, Jenna! I had a job as a bather in a dog salon and the experienced groomers said that greyhounds skin is like thin, fragile glass. I felt horrible because I was brand new and had no idea and had this greyhound up on the drying bed and she bailed like no dog I’ve ever seen react so severely before and I caught her because she was still attached to the bed with the noose. Her leg got cut and I thought it was basically the end of the world, I was freaking out. But apparently it’s pretty common and happens a lot but I don’t understand why nobody had warned me beforehand. Some dogs need specific instructions and care and this breed in particular is very delicate and sensitive. It’s a privilege and a reward to be dog owners and you’ve earned it well. It’s also not an easy job, but worth it to adopt a rescue. I’m happy Bunny has her people she can trust now 😍
snippet.textOriginal: You did so well, Jenna! I had a job as a bather in a dog salon and the experienced groomers said that greyhounds skin is like thin, fragile glass. I felt horrible because I was brand new and had no idea and had this greyhound up on the drying bed and she bailed like no dog I’ve ever seen react so severely before and I caught her because she was still attached to the bed with the noose. Her leg got cut and I thought it was basically the end of the world, I was freaking out. But apparently it’s pretty common and happens a lot but I don’t understand why nobody had warned me beforehand. Some dogs need specific instructions and care and this breed in particular is very delicate and sensitive. It’s a privilege and a reward to be dog owners and you’ve earned it well.
